description: Deletes a DBProxyEndpoint. Doing so removes the ability to access the DB proxy using the endpoint that you defined. The endpoint that you delete might have provided capabilities such as read/write or read-only operations, or using a different VPC than the DB proxy's default VPC.

parameters.name: DBProxyEndpointName
parameters.description: The name of the DB proxy endpoint to delete.

nested_items.name: DBProxyEndpoint
nested_items.description: The data structure representing the details of the DB proxy endpoint that you delete.

nested_items.name: DBProxyEndpointName
nested_items.description: The name for the DB proxy endpoint. An identifier must begin with a letter and must contain only ASCII letters, digits, and hyphens; it can't end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens.

nested_items.name: DBProxyEndpointArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB proxy endpoint.

nested_items.name: DBProxyName
nested_items.description: The identifier for the DB proxy that is associated with this DB proxy endpoint.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The current status of this DB proxy endpoint. A status of available means the endpoint is ready to handle requests. Other values indicate that you must wait for the endpoint to be ready, or take some action to resolve an issue.

nested_items.name: VpcId
nested_items.description: Provides the VPC ID of the DB proxy endpoint.

nested_items.name: VpcSecurityGroupIds
nested_items.description: Provides a list of VPC security groups that the DB proxy endpoint belongs to.

nested_items.name: VpcSubnetIds
nested_items.description: The EC2 subnet IDs for the DB proxy endpoint.

nested_items.name: Endpoint
nested_items.description: The endpoint that you can use to connect to the DB proxy. You include the endpoint value in the connection string for a database client application.

nested_items.name: CreatedDate
nested_items.description: The date and time when the DB proxy endpoint was first created.

nested_items.name: TargetRole
nested_items.description: A value that indicates whether the DB proxy endpoint can be used for read/write or read-only operations.

nested_items.name: IsDefault
nested_items.description: Indicates whether this endpoint is the default endpoint for the associated DB proxy. Default DB proxy endpoints always have read/write capability. Other endpoints that you associate with the DB proxy can be either read/write or read-only.
